<div class="row g-4">
  <div class="col-lg-8 mx-auto">
    <nav aria-label="breadcrumb" class="mb-3">
      <ol class="breadcrumb"><li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="/">Home</a></li><li class="breadcrumb-item active">Cookie Policy</li></ol>
    </nav>

    <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm p-4 p-md-5">
      <div class="d-flex align-items-center gap-3 mb-4">
        <span style="background:var(--gradient);width:48px;height:48px;border-radius:12px;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0;">
          <i class="bi bi-cookie text-white fs-5"></i>
        </span>
        <div>
          <h1 class="h3 fw-bold mb-0">Cookie Policy</h1>
          <p class="text-muted small mb-0">Last updated: January 2025</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-content">
        <p class="lead">This Cookie Policy explains what cookies are, how ApolloNews uses them, and how you can control them.</p>

        <h4 class="fw-bold mt-4">1. What Are Cookies?</h4>
        <p>Cookies are small text files placed on your device when you visit a website. They allow the website to recognise your device on subsequent visits and store certain preferences or information. Cookies do not contain personally identifiable information by themselves, but they may be linked to personal information we hold about you.</p>

        <h4 class="fw-bold mt-4">2. Types of Cookies We Use</h4>

        <div class="table-responsive mt-3">
          <table class="table table-bordered table-sm">
            <thead class="table-dark">
              <tr><th>Category</th><th>Cookie</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Duration</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td><strong>Essential</strong></td><td>connect.sid</td><td>Session management (keeps you logged in as admin)</td><td>Session</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Preferences</strong></td><td>cookieConsent</td><td>Stores your cookie consent choice</td><td>1 year</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Analytics</strong></td><td>_ga, _gid</td><td>Google Analytics — measures site traffic and user behaviour (anonymised)</td><td>Up to 2 years</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Advertising</strong></td><td>DSID, IDE, __gads</td><td>Google AdSense — serves relevant advertisements and measures ad performance</td><td>Up to 13 months</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <h4 class="fw-bold mt-4">3. Essential Cookies</h4>
        <p>Essential cookies are necessary for the Site to function correctly. They enable core features such as security, session management, and accessibility. You cannot opt out of essential cookies while continuing to use the Site.</p>

        <h4 class="fw-bold mt-4">4. Analytics Cookies (Google Analytics)</h4>
        <p>We use Google Analytics to understand how visitors engage with our Site — which pages are most visited, how long users stay, and how they navigate. All data is anonymised; we do not share personally identifiable information with Google Analytics.</p>
        <p>You can opt out of Google Analytics tracking by installing the <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Analytics opt-out browser add-on</a>.</p>

        <h4 class="fw-bold mt-4">5. Advertising Cookies (Google AdSense)</h4>
        <p>We partner with Google AdSense to display advertisements. Google and its advertising partners use cookies to serve ads based on your prior visits to this or other websites. These cookies help ensure the ads you see are relevant to your interests.</p>
        <p>To opt out of interest-based advertising, visit:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Ads Settings</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://optout.aboutads.info/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Digital Advertising Alliance</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://www.youronlinechoices.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Your Online Choices (EU)</a></li>
        </ul>

        <h4 class="fw-bold mt-4">6. How to Control Cookies</h4>
        <p>You can control and delete cookies through your browser settings. Instructions for the most common browsers:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Chrome</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/enhanced-tracking-protection-firefox" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Mozilla Firefox</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT201265" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Apple Safari</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-edge/delete-cookies-in-microsoft-edge-63947406-40ac-c3b8-57b9-2a946a29ae09" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Microsoft Edge</a></li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-muted small">Note: Disabling cookies may affect the functionality of this and many other websites you visit.</p>

        <h4 class="fw-bold mt-4">7. Changes to This Policy</h4>
        <p>We may update this Cookie Policy to reflect changes in technology, regulation, or our practices. We will post the updated policy on this page with a revised date.</p>
      </div>
